node.text: Biden said we had no choice but to leave Afghanistan. He’s right. There was no reason to stay there. The question is, how exactly do you get out? Just because something is necessary doesn’t mean you get to ignore the details. If you learned you needed an emergency appendectomy, would it matter to you whether your surgeon was a physician with a scalpel, or a drunk guy with a pocket knife? Yes, it would matter. But it didn’t matter to Joe Biden. He did the necessary thing in the ugliest possible way.

node.text: There are too many lies about Hungary in the media. We’ve watched all of this from the United States, and wondered if what we’d heard could be true. This week we came to Hungary to see for ourselves. We sat down with Orbán for a couple of long conversations.

node.title: Hungarian PM Viktor Orbán Talks To Tucker

node.text: Biden said we had no choice but to leave Afghanistan. He’s right. There was no reason to stay there. The question is, how exactly do you get out? Just because something is necessary doesn’t mean you get to ignore the details. If you learned you needed an emergency appendectomy, would it matter to you whether your surgeon was a physician with a scalpel, or a drunk guy with a pocket knife? Yes, it would matter. But it didn’t matter to Joe Biden. He did the necessary thing in the ugliest possible way.

node.text: Join Tucker for a live online book signing of his new book on Wednesday, August 11th at 3pm ET. Go to PremiereCollectibles.com/thelongslide to purchase your copy of The Long Slide: Thirty Years in American Journalism and ask Tucker a question that he can answer during the signing.

node.text: There are too many lies about Hungary in the media. We’ve watched all of this from the United States, and wondered if what we’d heard could be true. This week we came to Hungary to see for ourselves. We sat down with Orbán for a couple of long conversations.
